Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe welcomed US Vice President Mike Pence to Japan, expressing his belief that the alliance between the two countries has grown stronger. He emphasized the need for cooperation in addressing the challenges posed by North Korea and other issues in the Asia region. Pence echoed Abe's sentiments, stating that the US-Japan alliance is crucial for peace and security in the Indo-Pacific. He assured Japan that the US stands with them in addressing the threat from North Korea and achieving the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. Both leaders expressed their eagerness to strengthen economic and cultural ties between the two countries.